Okay, I thought the question was about fears. Now Mr. Sheen, how do you keep those kids off of your lawn?

Well gee whiz first I warned them off, then I went out and I, you know, escorted them out. I tried setting up lines of fire. But when that didn't work I had to shoot a bunch of kids, which is a real shame. But in such an area it was called necessary.

Excellent. How did you feel when you first became one of the contestants in the U-BALD first annual Folktale Fest?

Well let's see. When I first was accepted into the contest I was... excited! I immediately booked a trip to Syria, picked up my running shoes and ate up a banana royally because I was just so happy. I ran over there and threw my Congo Courier at the counter clerk and just shouted "YOU GUYS ARE LIKE, THE GREATEST! YEAH!" And then I immediately went to the first gathering ever of the Folktale Fest as a participant, as was invited, and took up Nitro Blast to keep me going for like 48 years. It was great! And I'm so excited to be a participant in another festival right now, so here I am.
